thought.text: Great! Let me also test the LaTeX and pretty printers:

action.command:
cd /tmp/tmpyjyraizy/sympy && python -c "
from sympy import MatrixSymbol, latex, pprint

A = MatrixSymbol('A', 2, 2)
B = MatrixSymbol('B', 2, 2)
C = MatrixSymbol('C', 2, 2)

print('=== Testing all printers ===')

# Test basic addition
expr = A + B
print(f'A + B:')
print(f'  str(): {str(expr)}')
print(f'  latex(): {latex(expr)}')

# Test subtraction
expr = A - B
print(f'A - B:')
print(f'  str(): {str(expr)}')
print(f'  latex(): {latex(expr)}')

# Test complex expression
expr = A + B - C
print(f'A + B - C:')
print(f'  str(): {str(expr)}')
print(f'  latex(): {latex(expr)}')

print('All printer tests passed!')
"
